["World's End Harem (Japanese: \u7d42\u672b (\u3057\u3085\u3046\u307e\u3064)\u306e\u30cf\u30fc\u30ec\u30e0 , Hepburn: Sh\u016bmatsu no H\u0101remu)  is a Japanese manga series written by LINK and illustrated by Kotaro Sh\u014dno. It began serialization in Shueisha's digital magazine Sh\u014dnen Jump+ in May 2016.","An anime television series adaptation by Studio Gokumi and AXsiZ is scheduled to premiere in 2021.","In the year 2040, Reito Mizuhara is suffering from a rare disease and is put into cryostasis while waiting for a life-saving treatment to be developed. Five years later, Reito awakens and learns that while he was asleep, the world was struck by the MK (Man Killing) Virus that caused the death of every male human in the planet, except for around one million survivors put in cryostasis before being infected. Much to his surprise, Reito learns that he is one of five males in Japan who somehow developed immunity to the MK Virus and is \"forced\" to take part in a reproduction program to ensure humanity's survival.","While Reito investigates the secrets surrounding the MK Virus and the mysterious disappearance of his girlfriend, Elisa, the series also shows the perspective of the other men who developed immunity to the virus, each with their own circumstances.","World's End Harem is written by LINK and illustrated by Kotaro Sh\u014dno. It started on Shueisha's digital magazine Sh\u014dnen Jump+ on May 8, 2016.[5] In May 2020, it was announced that the first part of the manga reached its climax.[6] The first part of the manga finished with its 85th chapter on June 21, 2020.[7] The manga has been compiled into individual tank\u014dbon by Shueisha. The first volume was published on September 2, 2016.[8] As of August 4, 2020, twelve volumes have been released.[9]","Seven Seas Entertainment announced the acquisition of the manga in October 2017. It is being published under its Ghost Ship imprint for mature readers.[10]","A related series, titled World's End Harem: Fantasia started in Shueisha's Ultra Jump on April 19, 2018.[11]","A spin-off by Kira Et\u014d, titled World's End Harem: Britannia Lumi\u00e9re, started on Sh\u014dnen Jump+ and Manga Mee app on June 26, 2020.[12] In December 2020, the series went on hiatus after it 17th chapter due to Et\u014d's health condition.[13]","In May 2020, it was announced that the series will receive an anime television series adaptation.  The series is animated by Studio Gokumi and AXsiZ, with Yuu Nobuta as director and Tatsuya Takahashi as scriptwriter.  Masaru Koseki is designing the characters, while Shigenobu Ookawa is composing the series' music.[3]  It will premiere in 2021.[2]","As of November 2018, the first seven volumes of the manga had over 3 million copies in circulation.[35]"]